FL Studio 7 is no longer the fringe audio workstation that it once was. With version 7,
it has matured into a true competitor for such applications as Cubase, Sonar, and even Pro Tools

In this VTC tutorial, Author Sam McGuire, helps beginners navigate the FL Studio application,
while still providing tips and tricks that the experienced user will find useful.
Not only does Sam cover the basic functionality, but also provides real world applications.
Using FL Studio to create music is the goal, and this tutorial helps users create a seamless and transparent environment.
If you want to become a FL Studio expert, this tutorial provides the means.
